canonical:
  title: 元正答北界兵馬使賀
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 營柳搖金方迓首春之候溪藤鍊雪遠移手墨之華恭惟某官邈自雲霄出臨關塞鎭如山重天子無復北憂威若雷行胡雛不敢南牧適丁令旦丕擁美祥某燮理無能論思忝位方欲修於賀牘遽先及於賢書奉戴已還欣榮交切
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 元正答北界兵馬使賀
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 營柳搖金。方迓首春之候。溪藤鍊雪。遠移手墨之華。恭惟某官。邈自雲霄。出臨關塞。鎭如山重。天子無復北憂。威若雷行。胡雛不敢南牧。適丁令旦。丕擁美祥。某燮理無能。論思忝位。方欲修於賀牘。遽先及於賢書。奉戴已還。欣榮交切。
korean:
  title: 원정 답 북계병마사 하
  author: 이규보
  language: kor
  text: 군영(軍營)의 버들이 금빛을 흔드니 바야흐로 첫봄의 기후를 만났는데, 계등(溪藤)의 종이가 눈같이 희어 멀리 빛나는 묵적(墨跡)을 띠고 왔구려. 삼가 생각하건대, 모관(某官)은 대궐로부터 멀리 나와 변방에 좌정하시니, 안정감이 산처럼 무거움에 천자는 다시 북쪽의 근심이 없고, 위엄이 우레같이 시행될 것이니 되놈들은 감히 남으로 침략을 못하리다. 마침 신년을 맞아서 크게 아름다운 상서 누리소서. 모(某)는 음양을 섭리(燮理)할 능력이 없이 논사(論思)의 자리를 더럽히고 있을 뿐입니다. 방금 하장(賀狀)을 보내려 하던 차에 문득 현서(賢書)가 먼저 이르니, 반갑게 받아보고 기쁨과 영광이 아울러 간절하나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0510_010_0500&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Response to the Congratulations from the Commander of the Northern Border
  author: Lee Gyeou-bo
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The willows of the military camp sway with golden light as spring's first breath arrives. The paper of the mountain stream glistens white as snow, bearing distant traces of noble brushwork.

    I humbly consider: you, honored official, have journeyed far from the court's distant halls to garrison the mountain passes. Your presence settles heavy as stone—the Son of Heaven no longer worries of the north. Your authority moves like thunder—the northern riders dare not venture south to plunder.

    As fortune would have it, the new year arrives bearing great blessings and auspicious omens. Yet I, lacking the virtue to balance heaven and earth, merely disgrace my position in the councils of thought. I had intended to send congratulations through proper dispatch when suddenly your gracious letter arrived before mine. To receive it brings such delight—joy and honor flood my heart at once.
  footnotes:
    - This is a diplomatic poem-letter expressing gratitude for received congratulations while offering formal praise for the recipient's military service and governance. It exemplifies the refined courtly correspondence style of Goryeo's literati.
    - The imagery of willows, snow, and spring reflects the seasonal context of New Year's greetings, while military and celestial metaphors emphasize the recipient's power and benevolence.
